  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the implementation of the Guidelines to Protect Migrants in Countries Experiencing Conflict or Natural Disaster Through Knowledge Transfer and Capacity Building</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following the launch of the &#x201C;Guidelines to Protect Migrants in Countries Experiencing Conflict or Natural Disaster&#x201D; (MICIC Guidelines), in June 2016, IOM has actively worked to disseminate and socialize their content through targeted fora of policymakers, practitioners and academics. IOM has also actively engaged in support of their implementation, through the development and roll out of capacity building tools, in cooperation with selected governmental counterparts in countries of origin and destination.</narrative>
  </description>
